  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1982-03-31", 
    "text": "Amends the Ethics in Government Act of 1978 to require Members of Congress and candidates for such offices to include a copy of their most recent Federal income tax return with their financial disclosure report. Requires Members and candidates to report the actual dollar value of items disclosed, in lieu of categories of value. Directs the Comptroller General to conduct systematic random audits of reports filed by Members under this Act."
